node.text: Videos showing people smuggling migrants past Border Patrol checkpoints and flashing thousands of dollars in cash are being posted on TikTok, Texas State Troopers say. This is a new and dangerous tactic to recruit teens to drive migrants from the US-Mexico border to Houston and other Texas cities — with one video offering $4,500 per person they smuggle. CNN's @rosaflorescnn reports.

node.title: Mexican cartels are recruiting teens on TikTok to smuggle migrants

node.text: Take a look at Tokyo’s Olympic Village, a city within a city where elite athletes from all over the world will spend their time when they’re not competing for Olympic gold. But the pandemic means things look very different to Olympic Villages of the past, as @selinawangtv finds out.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 20, 2021. May be an image of 1 person, standing and text that says 'Angelina Jolie joins Instagram to call attention to the suffering in Afghanistan UNHCR ion on'.

node.text:
Angelina Jolie, a notoriously private celebrity with no public social media presence, joined Instagram on Friday. She said she plans to use the platform to draw attention to the situation in Afghanistan by sharing the stories of people "who are fighting for their basic human rights."⁠
⁠
(📸: Olympa de Maismont/AFP/Getty Images)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 20, 2021. May be an image of text that says '" No one trusts anything that comes from the Taliban's mouth." CNN Three women describe Afghanistan under the Taliban'.

node.text:
CNN reached three women — all in their mid-20s and well-educated — to get a glimpse of how their lives have been impacted by the swift regime change and how they feel about their futures under Taliban rule. CNN is not using their names, for their own security.

Tap the link in our bio to read the full report.

node.text:
The US government is examining new locations, including in Europe, to relocate Afghans as it nears capacity in Qatar and scrambles to address the crush of people looking to flee Afghanistan, sources told CNN Friday.⁠
⁠
Tap the link in our bio for live updates.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 20, 2021. May be an image of sky and text that says 'Rain fell at the normally snowy summit of Greenland for the first time time on record CNN'.

node.text:
For the first time on record, it rained — not snowed — on Saturday at the summit of Greenland, roughly two miles above sea level. Temperatures at the summit over the weekend rose above freezing for the third time in less than a decade, and the amount of ice mass lost on Sunday was seven times higher than normal for this time of year.⁠
⁠
(📸: Uriel Sinai/Getty Images/2007)

node.text:
Just when you thought your work meetings could not get any worse, Facebook wants to do them in VR. Horizon Workrooms is a free app you can use with the Oculus Quest 2 headset, a device that starts at $299. Workrooms allow up to 16 VR headset users to meet in a virtual conference room, with each of them represented by a customizable cartoon-like avatar.

(📸: Shutterstock/Facebook)

node.text: Frantic Afghans looking to escape are struggling to get through Taliban checkpoints and into Kabul's airport. The US embassy in the city warned people on Wednesday evening that it cannot ensure safe passage to the airport. Right now, the Taliban controls the civilian side of the airport, including the road to the airport and the main entrance.⁠

node.text:
Polish javelin thrower Maria Andrejczyk auctioned off her Tokyo 2020 Olympic silver medal to fund a life-saving heart surgery for an eight-month-old baby. Żabka, a Polish supermarket chain, won the auction with a bid of $125,000, and then announced that it will be returning the medal to Andrejczyk.⁠
⁠
(📸: Martin Meissner/AP)⁠
